The paper discusses machine learning models for graph-structured data, specifically graph attention networks (GAT). This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of Machine Learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper proposes novel regularization strategies to improve the robustness of GAT models, which falls under the sub-category of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI). The use of deep learning solutions for graph-structured data also suggests that the paper could belong to the sub-category of Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE). The proposed strategies for improving robustness could also be considered as a form of security and privacy, which falls under the sub-category of Social and Information Networks (cs.SI). Finally, the paper uses benchmark datasets, which suggests that it could also belong to the sub-category of Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition (cs.CV).
